[thinking] **Analyzing Class Issues**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the potential ClassNotFoundException for a class not configured. In native-image, Class.forName with a constant string might work if the type is present. However, using newInstance may need that the class is registered for reflection. I wonder if the class must be known at build time. Also, the native environment may support reflective instantiation, provided all classes are included and registered correctly. There could be an UnsupportedFeatureError if not registered, but there's a lot here to unpack!
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Considering Adapter Access**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I'm thinking about the test class and its adapter, which may have package-private access. Class.newInstance requires the class to be public and have a public nullary constructor if it's in a different package. It seems that since RmicAdapterFactory in org.apache... calls newInstance, public access is necessary. I wonder if I can only have one top-level public class per file and whether public nested classes are possibly a solution. There’s a lot to navigate here!
